	(75, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'Bhashkar Yadav', '', 'http://twitter.com/bhashkar007', '', '127.0.0.1', 1363300560, NULL, 'Hi Aby,\n\n\nYes, it\'s captcha. You enabled captcha for registration from membership preferences. I tried to look within it but did get a full proof solution for it :( and still looking ....'),
	(76, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1371108720, NULL, 'Hi Charles,\n\nI would suggest you to use Freemember module for the registration process as this article approach wouldn\'t fulfill your all needs due to some EE behavior. \n\n\nYou can find Freemember from here: https://github.com/expressodev/freemember\n\n\n\nPlease let me know if you have any other question.\n\n\n\n\nThanks,\nBhashkar'),
	(77, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'Charles Gallant', 'charlesgallant@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1371103500, NULL, 'Hi Bhashkar, thanks for posting this.\n\nIt seems to add members to the site, although I can\'t seem to fix a few problems:\n\n1. The redirect doesn\'t seem to work; it takes me to a \'registration complete\' page living on the root of my site, ignoring the name=\"RET\" attribute value.\n\n2. The registration (\"activation\") email doesn\'t send.\n\nHave you (or any readers) found a way around these problems? Any tips on where to start looking?\n\n\n\nThanks in advance.'),
	(78, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'mwasimkhan', 'wasim.mkhan@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1461429840, NULL, 'i need to pass group id through form. how to do ?\nplease advise'),
	(79, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'mwasimkhan', 'wasim.mkhan@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1461432180, NULL, 'also custom field value not inserted into db. please advise'),
	(80, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'mwasimkhan', 'wasim.mkhan@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1461603060, NULL, 'Hi,\n\nI am out of \"custom field value\" issue &amp; now facing another problem\n&gt;&gt; I have setup auto activated for new member &amp;\n&gt;&gt; I logged with the admin and added a member through above code and after successfully submission , its replacing me with new created member on login in session \n\nPlease advice'),
	(81, 1, 35, 3, 0, 'o', 'URL', '', 'http://www.sGbKL9eID.net', '', '127.0.0.1', 1531762513, NULL, '<strong>... [Trackback]</strong>\n\n[...] Informations on that Topic: sidd3.com/stand-alone-member-registration-form-in-expressionengine/ [...]'),
	(82, 1, 40, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1376501160, NULL, 'Hi Rick,\n\nThanks for reading this post.\n\nYes, its possible with JavaScript. We can fetch product\'s SKU from URL and pass in JS variable which can be used for your further needs.\nI think, the product pages URL will be in same pattern for all the products as reference URL which you shared.\n\nThanks,'),
	(83, 1, 40, 3, 0, 'o', 'Rick Dronkers', 'rick.dronkers@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1376502360, NULL, 'Yeah the format is the same on the whole site.'),
	(84, 1, 40, 3, 0, 'o', 'Rick Dronkers', 'rick.dronkers@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1376495100, NULL, 'Hi Bhashkar,\n\n\nI Stumbled upon your posts through Google.\n\n\nI\'m implementing Google Tag Manager on a website and need to fetch the past part of a URL for usage in tag manager.\n\n\nExample:\nhttp://www.website.com/category/subcategory/awesome-product-name-123456.aspx\n\n\nI need to fetch the 123456 part (the product SKU) without the product name and without .aspx. Do you think you could help me out?'),
	(85, 1, 42, 3, 0, 'o', 'Electric Labs', '', 'http://twitter.com/electriclabs', '', '127.0.0.1', 1367350260, NULL, 'Hi Bhashkar,\n\n\nThis looks really useful. Thanks!\n\n\nRob'),
	(86, 1, 43, 3, 0, 'o', 'Entry Revisions (Plugin) | Sidd3', '', 'http://www.sidd3.com/entry-revisions-plugin/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1381537997, NULL, '[&#8230;] I have written an article Get entry revisions in ExpressionEngine for getting entry revisions with PHP code but it would be difficult for the guys not having PHP [&#8230;]'),
	(87, 1, 43, 3, 0, 'o', 'Entry Revisions (Plugin) &#8211; 360Adaptive Techn', '', 'http://ee2.sidd3.com/2019/01/19/entry-revisions-plugin-2/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1547900593, NULL, '[&#8230;] I wrote an article Get entry revisions in ExpressionEngine for getting entry revisions with PHP code, but it would be difficult for the those not having PHP [&#8230;]'),
	(88, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Get entry revisions in ExpressionEngine | Sidd3', '', 'http://www.sidd3.com/get-entry-revisions-in-expressionengine/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1382117732, NULL, '[&#8230;] Note: I developed a plugin Entry Revisions. It would be better to use [&#8230;]'),
	(89, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'lukedavid', 'ldavid20@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1404163920, NULL, 'Does this plugin exist any longer? The link is broken and it seems to be exactly what I am looking for!'),
	(90, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1404170100, NULL, 'Please try to download now. I corrected the download link.'),
	(91, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Laurence', 'info@amitywebsolutions.co.uk', 'http://www.amitywebsolutions.co.uk/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1411263300, NULL, 'This is good! Except... what about adding in the ability to fetch a specific revision? Because I would like to link the revisions to view that revision on the front end. But cant see how. \nThanks'),
	(92, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Laurence', 'info@amitywebsolutions.co.uk', 'http://www.amitywebsolutions.co.uk/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1411263960, NULL, 'I\'ve done it on the plugin, I did this....\n\n\nAdd this on line 47:\n\n		// Parameter # version_date [Optional]\n$version_date = $this-&gt;EE-&gt;TMPL-&gt;fetch_param(\'version_date\', 0);\n\nAdd this on line 81:\n\n		if( $version_date )\n			$cond .= \" AND 360_entry_versioning.version_date IN (\'\".str_replace(\'|\', \"\',\'\", $this-&gt;EE-&gt;db-&gt;escape_str($version_date)).\"\')\";\n\nNow we can add this in the revisions tag:\nversion_date=\"{segment_4}\"'),
	(93, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Jamie', 'jammokablammo@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1413816360, NULL, 'The {revision:count} variable is set to 1 and never increased.\nI removed the $count variable and replaced revision:count around line 106 with:\n\n$tags[$k][\'revision:count\'] = $k + 1;'),
	(94, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Angela Vanlods', '', 'http://www.angievang22.com/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1478637186, NULL, '<strong>Nice website</strong>\n\nThis was very nice to develop such a nice website.'),
	(95, 1, 49, 3, 0, 'o', 'Zack', 'zack@mid.co.uk', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1490307840, NULL, 'Really useful plugin thanks. What would it take to create an ee3 version? :)'),
	(96, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'David Pak', 'david@csherpa.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385893800, NULL, 'This is great!\n\nA bit of a newb question but is there a way - or perhaps another plugin - that would combine the totals?'),
	(97, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385806200, NULL, 'Hi Martijn,\n\n\nThanks for letting me know.\n\n\nI have already added some more social share counts including Stumble and Delicious but couldn\'t get time to test and make public.\nWith it, I have some more updates in the plugin and hoping to update the plugin very soon.\n\n\nPlease keep me posted with your new ideas. \nYou can contact me via email bhashkar.yadav[at]live.com\n\n\nThanks,'),
	(98, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Martijn Broeders', 'martijn.gui@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385674200, NULL, 'Nice plugin. \n\nBut I am getting the following error:\n\nMessage: Undefined index: result\nFilename: social_share_count/pi.social_share_count.php\nLine Number: 158'),
	(99, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385678640, NULL, 'Hi Martijn,\n\nThanks for reporting the error.\n\nI have fixed the error and updated the plugin. Please download the updated copy of the plugin.\n\nPlease let me know if still having any issue.\n\nThanks,'),
	(100, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1396405200, NULL, 'Hi Justin,\n\nYes, you can use EE variables also. Please share if you \'re getting any issue in it.\n\nThanks,'),
	(101, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385898480, NULL, 'Hi David,\n\nThanks for using my plugin.\nWould you like to show the total of all counts. Please let me know. If you would to have any kind support related to this plugin, can contact directly via email at  bhashkar.yadav[at]live.com\n\nThanks,'),
	(102, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Justin Melton', 'justin.melton@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1396404720, NULL, 'Can you pass url variables to it? I.E. {site_url}, {url_title}, etc?  I\'m trying to use it with multiple articles on a page and want to get a count for each.'),
	(103, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Martijn Broeders', 'martijn.gui@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385681040, NULL, 'Yes, perfect. It works :-) thanks'),
	(104, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385681280, NULL, 'Your welcome Martijn.'),
	(105, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Martijn Broeders', 'martijn.gui@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1385743560, NULL, 'I have added stumble and delicious to your script. It works but I don\'t know if it\'s alright, code wise. Would you like a copy?'),
	(106, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Justin Melton', 'justin.melton@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1396404900, NULL, 'Being able to show combined totals is something I\'m interested in as well.'),
	(107, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1396405140, NULL, 'Hi Justin,\n\nThanks for using my plugin.\nSorry, I \'m in process to update this plugin and will launch the updated version very soon in which you would have such a facility also.\n\nThanks,'),
	(108, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Daniel Howells', 'daniel.howells@gmail.com', 'http://howells.ws/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1412130060, NULL, 'Hi! Did you get a chance to fix?'),
	(109, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Daniel Howells', 'daniel.howells@gmail.com', 'http://howells.ws/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1411056120, NULL, 'Hello! This morning a site started erroring with 504 errors. As soon as I removed the social share counts for facebook and twitter, it started working again. Are there any problems as far as you know?'),
	(110, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'bhashkar007', 'bhashkar007@gmail.com', '', '', '127.0.0.1', 1411059480, NULL, 'Hi Daniel,\n\n\nThanks for letting me know. I \'ll fix it tonight and let you know so that you can download the updated plugin.\n\n\nThanks'),
	(111, 1, 50, 3, 0, 'o', 'Daniel Howells', 'daniel.howells@gmail.com', 'http://howells.ws/', '', '127.0.0.1', 1411059540, NULL, 'Wonderful - thanks so much.'),
